 ./cluster_compression_test.sh 128
panel scale: NS=128 ND=42 per fault; admissibility eta=2.0 tol=1e-5 leaf=8

=== 1. clustering: joint geometric tree vs split-by-fault (matched accuracy) ===
case             N    joint_x    split_x      gain  verdict
parallel     10752      6.02x      6.00x     -0.3%  geometric ok
divergent    10752      5.61x      5.97x     +6.4%  split helps
cross        10752      5.37x      6.57x    +22.3%  split helps
separated    10752     11.53x     11.53x     +0.0%  geometric ok

  joint_x/split_x = dense/stored compression; gain = (split-joint)/joint.
  positive gain means isolating the faults stores less (helps).

=== 2. backend compressibility on the joint operator (np=1) ===
case             N     htool    hacapk     hmmvp
single        5376  6.113080      5.06    10.385
parallel     10752  5.414794      4.90    10.814
divergent    10752  5.053096      4.74     11.46
cross        10752  4.668618      4.92    10.723
separated    10752 11.972493      9.51    19.957

  values are compression ratio (dense/H-matrix); >1 compresses, <=1 near-dense.
  small N compresses little for every backend; raise SCALE to see the trend.
